public class QueryVariable
extends com.hp.hpl.jena.rdf.model.impl.ResourceImpl
implements com.hp.hpl.jena.rdf.model.Resource

A QueryVariable represents a variable in a ModelQuery pattern and can be used to extract values from the results of a ModelQuery.run().

QueryVariables are constructed using the ModelQuery.createVariable() methods.

value

public com.hp.hpl.jena.rdf.model.RDFNode value(java.util.List<com.hp.hpl.jena.graph.Node> values)
Answer the value this QueryVariable identifies in the result binding list values, which should be an element from an iterator generated by run() on this QueryVariable's parent().

literal

public com.hp.hpl.jena.rdf.model.Literal literal(java.util.List<com.hp.hpl.jena.graph.Node> values)
Answer the Literal value this QueryVariable identifies in the result binding values. If the underlying node is not a literal, throw an exception. values should be an element from an iterator generated by run() on this QueryVariable's parent().

resource

public com.hp.hpl.jena.rdf.model.Resource resource(java.util.List<com.hp.hpl.jena.graph.Node> values)
Answer the Resource value this QueryVariable identifies in the result binding values. If the underlying node is not a Resource, throw an exception. values should be an element from an iterator generated by run() on this QueryVariable's parent().
